Patch Set 6: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve

Hey Kun,

Yeah it's not always obvious where/when to split up patches. I think in this case I see a couple.

1. Whitespace formatting in run_tests.sh

2. Adding glance stores to the docs

3. The paste-suffix thing in config

but this really isn't a big deal. Just seems like a logical split.

In other patches this can matter more because it can obscure the goal of the patch making it harder to review and it can make it harder to backport changes.
